Isaiah 30-32 And every stroke of the appointed staff that the LORD lays on them <f>ⓔ</f>will be to the sound of tambourines and lyres. <f>ⓕ</f>Battling with brandished arm, he will fight with them.
Isaiah 30-33 For <f>ⓖ</f>a burning place <f>[5]</f> has long been prepared; indeed, for the king it is made ready, <f>ⓗ</f>its pyre made deep and wide, with fire and wood in abundance; <f>ⓘ</f>the breath of the LORD, like a stream of sulfur, kindles it.